                        <div class="banner-image" >
                            <h1>Azure Service Health</h1>
                            <p>Personalized guidance and support for when issues in Azure services affect you.</p>
                            <p class="btn-ms"><a href="//portal.azure.cn/" target="_blank">Get Started<i class="icon icon-arrow-right"></i></a></p>
                            <p class="txt"><a href="//portal.azure.cn/#blade/Microsoft_Azure_Health/AzureHealthBrowseBlade/serviceIssues/">Already using Azure? View your personalized dashboard now<i class="icon icon-arrow-right"></i></a></p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div style="background:#323a45;height:60px;">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <p class="txt more-docs">Learn about Azure Service Health: <a href="//docs.azure.cn/zh-cn/service-health/" style="color:#00a3d9;margin-left:20px;">Documentation</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div> 
            <div class="solution-section" style="padding-bottom:60px;">
                <div class="container">         
                    <div class="row row-section">
                        <div class="col-md-1">
                            <img src="//resource.cdn.azure.cn/marketing-resource/css/images/service-health-setup.png" alt=""/>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-11">
                            <h2>Access a personalized dashboard</h2>
                            <p>Find timely information about service issues, periodic maintenance, and health reports for your resources directly from the Azure portal. A filtered view that helps you focus on what’s important is also provided.</p>
                            
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row row-section">
                        <div class="col-md-1">
                            <img src="//resource.cdn.azure.cn/marketing-resource/css/images/service-health-targeted.png" alt=""/>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-11">
                            <h2>Set up targeted notifications</h2>
                            <p>Azure Service Health integrates into Azure Monitor to notify you and your teams via email or webhook when your business-critical resources are affected.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row row-section">
                        <div class="col-md-1">
                            <img src="//resource.cdn.azure.cn/marketing-resource/css/images/service-health-support.png" alt=""/>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-11">
                            <h2>Receive guidance and support</h2>
                            <p>When an Azure issue affects your resources, Service Health helps you diagnose it and get support. You’ll receive constant updates on how Azure is fixing the issue until everything is resolved.</p>
                            
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-1">
                            <img src="//resource.cdn.azure.cn/marketing-resource/css/images/service-health-share.png" alt=""/>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-11">
                            <h2>Share details and updates easily</h2>
                            <p>Get a link for the issue to use in your problem management system, then download a PDF summary of the issue to share with people who don’t have access to the Azure portal.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
